# Numbered user environments

<script data-type="jmarkdown">
defineEnvironment('exercise', {
  numbered: true,
  html: (ctx) => `<aside class="exercise">${ctx.inner}</aside>`,
});
defineEnvironment('solution', {
  numbered: true,
  counter: 'exercise',
  html: (ctx) => `<aside class="solution">${ctx.inner}</aside>`,
});
</script>

See :ref[ex:one], :cref[ex:one], and :Cref[ex:two].

@begin(exercise)[Warm-up]{id=ex:one}
First exercise.
@end(exercise)

@begin(solution)
A solution, interleaving on the shared counter.
@end(solution)

